.SH NAME
pico-continuous \- Continuous authentication service for use with 
.B pam_pico
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B pico-continuous
.RI [ options ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
This manual page documents briefly the
.B pico-continuous
service.
.PP
The 
.B pico-continuous
service is usually run as a background service (daemon) and in its default 
configuration is set up to run at startup using 
.BR systemd (1) .
The 
.BR pam_pico (8)
authentication module interacts with the service by dbus and it's the 
service which actually performs the authentication and continuous 
authentication for the module. 
The service should be started, stopped and queried using 
.BR systemctl (1) .
See the 
.B examples 
section for how this can be done.
.PP
