.SH OPTIONS
This program follows the usual GNU command line syntax, with long
options starting with two dashes (`-').
However, currently
.B pico-continuous 
doesn't accept any options or parameters.
.SH EXAMPLES
The service should be started, stopped and queried using 
.BR systemctl (1)
. 
For example:
.TP
.B systemctl start pico-continuous
Start the continuous authentication service.
.TP
.B systemctl stop pico-continuous
Stop the continuous authentication service.
.TP
.B systemctl status pico-continuous
Query the status of the continuous authentication service.
